# Performance boundaries

See also: **`data-ownership.mdc`**, **`react-state-zustand.mdc`**, **`async-ui.mdc`**, **`api-layer.mdc`**.

AI often over-memoizes, mirrors huge server lists into Zustand, or renders unbounded tables. Prefer **correct ownership** and **bounded rendering** over premature optimization.

## Data placement (performance angle)

| Data                         | Owner              | Why                                      |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------ | ---------------------------------------- |
| Server lists & entities      | TanStack Query     | Cache, dedupe, pagination, invalidation  |
| Form fields                  | React Hook Form    | Isolated re-renders per field            |
| Local UI toggles             | `useState`         | Cheap, scoped                            |
| Cross-route client UI        | Zustand (small)    | Shared flags, auth mirror, layout prefs  |

**Do not** copy large Query results into Zustand ÔÇťfor performanceÔÇŁ ÔÇö that **duplicates** memory and fights invalidation (`data-ownership.mdc`).

```tsx
// Bad ÔÇö 10k users in global store; every subscriber re-renders on touch
const users = useStore((s) => s.users);
```

```tsx
// Good ÔÇö paginated query; page-sized slice in cache
const { data } = useUsers({ page, pageSize: 50 });
```

## TanStack Query cache

- **Paginate** large collections ÔÇö `page`, `limit`, cursor params in query key and API.
- **Do not** `setQueryData` with enormous arrays for ÔÇťoptimisticÔÇŁ or ÔÇťmerge all pagesÔÇŁ unless product requires it and UI is virtualized.
- Prefer **`useInfiniteQuery`** for incremental load; **do not** load entire history into one key.
- Use **`select`** in hooks to narrow subscribed data when a huge object is cached but the UI needs one field.

```typescript
return useQuery({
  queryKey: userKey(id),
  queryFn: () => fetchUser(id),
  select: (user) => ({ displayName: user.displayName, avatarUrl: user.avatarUrl }),
});
```

## Lists & tables

| Size              | Approach                                                |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| &lt; ~100 rows    | Normal render often fine                                |
| HundredsÔÇôthousands| **Virtualize** (`@tanstack/react-virtual` or table virtualizer) |
| Any large dataset | **Server pagination** or infinite scroll ÔÇö never fetch all upfront |

- Table sort/filter on big data Ôćĺ **server-side** when possible.
- Avoid `items.map` over unbounded arrays from a single query.

## Memoization discipline

**Do not memoize everything.** Default to plain render; optimize when profiling shows a problem.

| Use                                    | When                                                         |
| -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `useMemo` / `useCallback`              | Expensive pure compute; stable callback to memoized child  |
| `React.memo` on child                  | Child re-renders often with same props; parent updates a lot |
| `memo` on every leaf                   | **Avoid** ÔÇö noise, stale closure bugs                        |

**Red flags:**

- `useMemo(() => items.filter(...), [items])` on every small list without measurement
- `useCallback` wrapping every handler ÔÇťbecause best practiceÔÇŁ
- Zustand selector returning new object/array literals every call ÔÇö fix selector shape instead

```tsx
// Bad ÔÇö new object every time Ôćĺ useless memo
useStore((s) => ({ user: s.user, theme: s.theme }));
```

```tsx
// Good ÔÇö separate selectors or shallow compare only when needed
const user = useStore((s) => s.user);
```

## Effects & waterfalls

- Parallelize independent fetches in services (`Promise.all`) ÔÇö see `api-layer.mdc`.
- **Do not** serialize unrelated `await`s in one `queryFn` when calls are independent.
- Split dashboard regions into **separate queries** ÔÇö do not block the shell on the slowest widget (`interaction-polish.mdc` ┬ž11).

## Bundle & imports

- Prefer **direct imports** for heavy packages (icons, date libs) ÔÇö see `naming-conventions.mdc`.
- Lazy-load **routes** and heavy modals when the app grows (`React.lazy` + `Suspense`).

## Images & assets

- Use appropriate dimensions; lazy-load below-the-fold media.
- Do not inline megabyte assets in `src/`.

## Checklist

- [ ] Large collections are paginated or infinite-scrolled ÔÇö not fully loaded into one query key.
- [ ] No multi-thousand-row arrays in Zustand.
- [ ] Long lists use virtualization when rendering hundreds+ DOM nodes.
- [ ] Memoization added only for measured hotspots ÔÇö not by default on every component.
- [ ] Query `select` or narrow hooks used when subscribing to small slices of large cache entries.
